<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="E" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Errand" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Errand,</orth> 1) a verbal message: <bibl n="shak. err 2.1.72" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. II, 1, 72</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 4.3.6" default="NO" valid="yes">As IV, 3, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 3.1.137" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 1, 137</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.3.79" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 3, 79</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 2.4.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. II, 4, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 3.13.104" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 13, 104</bibl>. <cit><quote>to do an e.</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 4.4.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 4, 14</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>he came of an e.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.4.80" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 4, 80</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.4.114" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 4, 114</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.2.182" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 182</bibl>. <cit><quote>of a sleeveless e.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 5.4.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 4, 9</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>go a mile on his e.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 3.2.39" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 2, 39</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ado 2.1.273" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 1, 273</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 4.1.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. IV, 1, 13</bibl>.<lb />2) any oral communication to be made: <cit><quote>there is no lady living so meet for this great e.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 2.2.46" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. II, 2, 46</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>first I'll do my e.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 2.3.64" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 3, 64</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>upon which e. I now go toward him,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 5.1.231" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 231</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.1.69" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 1, 69</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.1.324" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 1, 324</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 5.2.65" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. V, 2, 65</bibl> (O. Edd. <emph>arrant</emph>).
